<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="21947" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="21947">Diagnosis</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="21947">Small (0.7-2.2 mm), convex flea beetles, with strongly developed jumping hind legs and characteristically clavate antennae. Frons is broad, antennal insertions widely separated. Antennae 11-segmented, clavate after the 3rd antennomere. The first three antennomeres are long and slender, the next three very small, the final five are enlarged and form a club. Pronotum with two setal pores, the anterior of which is placed behind the middle of the lateral margin. Metasternum with an anterior-pointing, broad processus. Posterior femora strongly dilated. Metatibia slender and with a long terminal spore and a row of smaller terminal setae on the lateral edge.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
